[1] Cholera - Nigeria
Date: Mon 25 Oct 2010
Source: The Washington Post, Associated Press (AP) report [edited]
<http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2010/10/25/AR2010102500657.html>


UN officials say Nigeria has seen more than 1500 deaths from cholera
in 2010, doubling the government's most recent fatality count.

Geneva-based UNICEF spokeswoman Marixie Mercado said Monday [25 Oct
2010] that as of 20 Oct 2010, there were 1555 deaths in Nigeria from
the waterborne disease, with 38 173 cases recorded in 2010 alone.

According to the WHO, the current outbreak is the worst in Nigeria
since 1991, when 7654 people died.

[Byline: John Gambrell]

