[2] Cholera - Benin
Date: Thu 21 Oct 2010
Source: AllAfrica, RFI report [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/201010211031.html>


Two thirds of the African nation of Benin is underwater, with at
least 43 people killed and nearly 100 000 made homeless.

Heavy rain began falling at the start of October 2010, and the Oueme
and Mono rivers soon overflowed. Thousands of hectares of land,
mostly used for growing rice and other vegetables are now underwater.

The UN's children's fund, UNICEF, reports 800 cases of cholera and
warns of the risk of other waterborne diseases.

--
