[5] Cholera - Nigeria (Sokoto)
Date: Thu 21 Oct 2010
Source: Nigerian Tribune [edited]
<http://www.tribune.com.ng/index.php/news/12422-cholera-claims-9-in-sokoto>


An outbreak of cholera at Lugu village, in Wurno Local Government
Area of Sokoto State, has claimed 9 lives from 7 Oct 2010. Nigerian
Tribune reported on Wednesday [20 Oct 2010] that the deceased
included children and adults.

It was also confirmed that the victims were from the isolation camp
set up in the village by the Medicines Sans Frontiers and assisted by
health officials from the Wurno Local Government Area. A local
government health official overseeing the operations of the camp,
Mallam Sambo Idris, said so far 1185 cases had been recorded at the camp.

[Byline: Bello Gusau]

